ctics that include surveillance, coercion, harassment and physical violence, transnational repression threatens the lives of democracy defenders, the basic rights of diaspora members and the rule of law in host states.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDissenters. 0aPolitical persecution. 4aIMES. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh1 aAdamson, Fiona B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaser, Bahar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöcü, Gözde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDukalskis, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurstenberg, Saipira , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFurstenberg, Saipira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlasius, Marlies, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrossman, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirt, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobbins, Meg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Gillian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLemon, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichaelsen, Marcus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohammad, Abdulkader Saleh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoss, Dana M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoss, Dana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPicard, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuinsaat, Sharon M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g